<TITLE> Rafiqur Rahman wins Reuters Journalist of the Year award </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 7 (bdnews24.com)Rafiqur Rahman, the principal television shooter for Reuters Television in Bangladesh, has won the prestigious Reuters Journalist of the Year Award. The London-based global news agency in a statement has said Rafiq has been declared 'Camera Operator of the Year 2007' for his hard work in the field of photojournalism. The agency said Rafiq's work on tumultuous political development, including declaration of state of emergency and days of curfew in 2007, has earned him the in-house award. "Reuters has been able to showcase remarkable, exclusive video coverage of Bangladesh through Rafiq's dedication to the story even in the most hazardous conditions," said David Schlesinger, Reuters editor-in-chief. Rafiq has been in photojournalism for 27 years. He has worked for various local newspapers before joining Reuters.
